1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:05,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:06,733
- [THUDS]
- You love meddling!

3
00:00:06,867 --> 00:00:08,067
Sir, please stop. That's enough!

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,933
If there's someone
to blame here, it's mom.

5
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:11,133
Please forgive me.

6
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:16,133
You watched my own father
disown me inside our own home!

7
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,333
I don't care.
As far as I'm concerned,

8
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:19,933
you're my only child now.

9
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:22,433
You're the only one who has
the right to carry my name.

10
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:24,833
Do what you need to do.

11
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:26,533
So, if Edward doesn't act,

12
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:28,467
why don't you act instead?

13
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,433
You don't need his permission

14
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:32,567
to claim
what's rightfully yours.

15
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:36,300
To my son, Paolo Torrecampo,

16
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:38,200
you are my legacy.

17
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,033
Wow!

18
00:00:40,167 --> 00:00:41,767
He doesn't deserve it, Dad.

19
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:45,567
He shouldn't be using
the Torrecampo surname.

20
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,367
What are you talking about?

21
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:52,833
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:12,533
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:34,800
How dare you!

24
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:36,567
Why did you go ahead of us?

25
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:37,767
You love interfering!

26
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:38,833
What is wrong with you, Paolo?

27
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:40,533
- That's enough!
- Paolo, stop it.

28
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,800
- Don't engage.
- Don't get mad at her.

29
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,800
If there's someone
to blame here, it's mom.

30
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,667
Because she lied to both of us.

31
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,767
Exactly.

32
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:52,233
Your mother who acts
like a saint.

33
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,833
But she's hiding a lot of dirt.

34
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:56,167
Paolo, please, don't engage!

35
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,733
- Paolo!
- Sir, please stop!

36
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,800
- Paolo!
- You're at the precinct.

37
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:01,267
Please show some respect.

38
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,767
If you don't stop,

39
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:05,467
I'll lock both of you up
in there!

40
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,033
Sir, I'm sorry.

41
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,500
I'll just talk to my sibling.

42
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:09,767
Stop this mess already.

43
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,800
My child, please let me explain.

44
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:17,800
To add to your sins even more?

45
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:20,700
You won't fool us again.

46
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:22,333
- Come on, Edward.
- Edward, please,

47
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:23,700
listen to your mother first.

48
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:26,700
Stop wasting time!

49
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:30,833
No explanation can justify
what you did to my spouse!

50
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:32,100
Can you please be quiet
for a moment?

51
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:36,867
Paolo, how long have you known
about this?

52
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,233
I only discovered it recently
too.

53
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:42,933
And believe me, we were planning
to tell you everything.

54
00:02:43,067 --> 00:02:44,900
That's why we came here.

55
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,933
Forgive me if I benefited

56
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:51,000
from all of dad's attention
and love.

57
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:56,633
I enjoyed the life
that was supposed to be yours.

58
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:58,633
And I'm deeply ashamed.

59
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:01,333
You did nothing wrong.

60
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,800
You were deceived too.

61
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:05,700
You're also a victim here.

62
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:11,033
Edward, my child.

63
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:14,567
I'm so sorry that I disrupted
both your lives as siblings.

64
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,267
I regret it now.

65
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,200
Please forgive me.

66
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:20,433
- Please.
- Just sorry?

67
00:03:22,367 --> 00:03:25,767
Just sorry for all the suffering
I had to endure

68
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:27,900
because of your lies?

69
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,667
Mom, you know this.

70
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,900
My life was a constant
struggle...

71
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,267
for dad's approval.

72
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,167
For his acceptance.

73
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:47,133
To prove myself worthy
of being a Torrecampo.

74
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:55,567
Yes, I know, you showed me love
and I had an ally in you.

75
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,167
But what was that?

76
00:03:58,733 --> 00:03:59,933
A consolation prize

77
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:03,233
because you took away the life
that I could have had?

78
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:06,733
It wasn't like that. It wasn't.

79
00:04:06,867 --> 00:04:08,433
It's exactly like that, Mom!

80
00:04:08,567 --> 00:04:09,933
It's exactly like that!

81
00:04:13,133 --> 00:04:15,433
You know what hurts the most?

82
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:19,467
That you could have done
something

83
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,567
that could have changed
the course of my life

84
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,933
if only you told the truth.

85
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:29,767
But instead,
you just watched me.

86
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:32,667
You watched me get disowned
by my own father

87
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,233
inside our own home!

88
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,700
I'm sorry, Mom.

89
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:42,067
I can't accept your apology.

90
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,467
My child.

91
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:48,633
The wound you caused
is too deep...

92
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:53,967
and I will never forgive you.

93
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:01,100
My child...

94
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:09,000
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
PLAYING]

95
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:30,600
[SIGHS]

96
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:31,967
- Dad.
- Yes?

97
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,133
I'm glad that you are
still awake.

98
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,900
May I talk to you?

99
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:40,200
There's...

100
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:42,700
If this is about
Edward's release,

101
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,033
don't continue.

102
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:45,767
I already heard.

103
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,367
How embarrassing.

104
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:53,300
Edward, this is the chance
we've been waiting for.

105
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:57,300
Your chance to take back
everything stolen from you.

106
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:00,933
I don't know, Thea.

107
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,567
I'm still confused.

108
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,433
Are you being for real?

109
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,967
Paolo is an illegitimate child.

110
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:14,267
In short, he has no right
to dad's wealth and position.

111
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:18,733
And once dad finds out,
you'll rise above him.

112
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:23,633
You'll become the golden boy
of the Torrecampos.

113
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:25,167
And Paolo?

114
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,100
Nothing.

115
00:06:26,233 --> 00:06:28,167
He'll be left in the gutter.

116
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:31,333
Everywhere I go, people ask me,

117
00:06:31,467 --> 00:06:33,967
"Why was that bastard released?"

118
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:39,367
But, Dad, it was proven again
that he wasn't guilty.

119
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:42,333
Miss Yolly already confessed
to everything.

120
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,500
And you think that's enough?

121
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:46,367
But Paolo is still my brother.

122
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:50,767
We can't forget that he helped
with Ashley's operation.

123
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,933
We can't ignore that.

124
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:54,133
[TUTS]

125
00:06:54,267 --> 00:06:55,200
What?

126
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,800
- [THUDS]
- Don't be an idiot!

127
00:06:57,933 --> 00:07:01,667
They only did that
to protect themselves.

128
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:04,833
So they wouldn't be sued
for using Ashley.

129
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:09,200
It's not enough that
Miss Yolly alone rots in jail.

130
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:10,900
She should've dragged
Edward down too

131
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:12,800
to ease my headache.

132
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,867
Dad, Edward is innocent.

133
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,600
He's a victim.

134
00:07:17,733 --> 00:07:19,467
I don't care.

135
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:23,067
Innocent or not,
I no longer care about him.

136
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,033
I will never accept him again
in this house.

137
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:29,300
He's a disgrace
to the Torrecampo name.

138
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:31,467
Don't blame Paolo.

139
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:34,767
He only found out recently.

140
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:36,567
But he benefited.

141
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:41,100
While you were disowned
and almost rotted in jail.

142
00:07:41,233 --> 00:07:46,900
There's Paolo, enjoying himself
as the golden boy.

143
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:50,400
How long will you keep
being the good boy, Edward?

144
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:52,600
When will you stop tolerating
being treated

145
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:55,767
like a rag by the Torrecampos?

146
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:58,100
Good thing you're here, Paolo.

147
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:01,733
As far as I'm concerned,

148
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:04,100
you're my only child now.

149
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:08,733
You're the only one who has
the right to carry my name.

150
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:14,067
And now, what will you say?

151
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,733
Make it quick.

152
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:17,167
I want to rest already.

153
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:18,600
It's...

154
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:28,533
Edward, think about our family.

155
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:31,200
Think about Ashley.

156
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,367
It's nothing, Dad.

157
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:39,633
It's just about tomorrow
for the board meeting.

158
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:42,900
It's nothing. We can just talk
about it tomorrow in the office.

159
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:46,900
Do what you need to do.

160
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:48,867
Even if only for your child.

161
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:56,067
Okay.

163
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,800
Good night, everyone.

164
00:09:04,467 --> 00:09:09,733
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:23,267
["KATOTOHANAN"
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:09:36,467 --> 00:09:39,133
["KATOTOHANAN"
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,433
I feel sorry for Jasmine
and Ashley.

168
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,233
They're still so young.

169
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:01,267
And they've already been
through a lot.

170
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,600
[SOBS]

171
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:06,800
With everything
that's happening now...

172
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:10,433
I hope you realize
the consequences

173
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:13,100
of your wrong choices.

174
00:10:13,233 --> 00:10:16,633
If only you hadn't given in
to temptation back then.

175
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,133
If only you hadn't been weak,

176
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:22,467
the children wouldn't be
suffering.

177
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,233
So don't be angry
at your mother.

178
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,100
Because you have no right.

179
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:32,333
You were both weak.

180
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:39,933
I know my mistakes.

181
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:47,467
That's why I'll do my best
to give Jasmine and Ashley

182
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,967
the happiness they deserve.

183
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:55,200
Paolo, this problem
won't fix itself.

184
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:59,200
We need to tell your father
before this gets worse.

185
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,367
[SIGHS]

186
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:04,067
I'm just worried.

187
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:07,533
What if the opposite happens?

188
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,267
You heard him earlier,
didn't you?

189
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,600
He really believes in me.

190
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:17,367
What if he finds out that...

191
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,267
I'm actually illegitimate?

192
00:11:20,733 --> 00:11:23,367
He'd probably disown me.

193
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:26,867
What if you're also thrown out
of this mansion?

194
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,367
Remove me from the company?

195
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:33,433
What about
the children's future?

196
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,533
Paolo, we have to do it.

197
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:40,933
We have to do it for our kids.

198
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:45,500
Do you want them to grow up
surrounded by lies?

199
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:50,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:57,000
Thank you again
for the information you gave us.

201
00:11:57,133 --> 00:12:00,300
At least now I've proven
that you can be trusted.

202
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:02,800
But why do you still look
so upset?

203
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:07,867
Shouldn't you and your spouse
be celebrating?

204
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,533
Since you now have an advantage
over Paolo?

205
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:14,600
[GRUMBLES]

206
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,967
That's exactly the problem.

207
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,633
Edward is still hesitating.

208
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,700
- [CHUCKLES]
- He's too soft

209
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,800
when it comes to Paolo.

210
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:26,133
I keep telling him
this is our chance to rise.

211
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,267
But he won't listen to me.

212
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:35,467
You're too overqualified
for a spouse with no ambition.

213
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,733
At least laugh.

214
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,133
What the hell are you doing?

215
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:43,367
What is wrong with you?

216
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:47,367
I've done my research on you,
Thea.

217
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,033
You're a go getter.

218
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:55,167
You'll do anything
to get what you want.

219
00:12:57,267 --> 00:13:00,033
So, if Edward doesn't act,

220
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:02,433
why don't you do it yourself?

221
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,067
You don't need his permission

222
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,633
to claim
what's rightfully yours.

223
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:11,833
But how am I supposed to do
that?

224
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,867
Dad is angry at me.

225
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,833
He doesn't want to see
or talk to me.

226
00:13:16,967 --> 00:13:19,633
He even blocked
all my access to him.

227
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,200
Well, lucky for you.

228
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:27,133
I know exactly
where he'll be tonight.

229
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:31,467
He has an awarding event
to attend.

230
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:34,800
I'm sure he won't be able
to avoid you,

231
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:37,233
in front of many people.

232
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:41,967
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

233
00:13:52,267 --> 00:13:53,167
Thank you.

234
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,133
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

235
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,433
- Paolo.
- Thank you.

236
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:58,300
Yes, Marj?

237
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,367
Have you told dad already?

238
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,133
Not yet.

239
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:07,333
But I'll tell him
after this event.

240
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:11,067
Look at him.

241
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,700
He's so happy.

242
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,833
This is the first time
I've seen him like this

243
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:19,233
after everything
that happened at home.

244
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:21,967
At the company.

245
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:28,167
Pao, didn't we agree
we'd tell him the truth

246
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,333
before someone else does?

247
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:32,000
I know.

248
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,133
But I don't want
to ruin his mood

249
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:37,833
on the night he receives
an award.

250
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:41,967
Can we please just give him
this moment...

251
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,533
before we break his heart?

252
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:47,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:49,500
Mom.

254
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,500
What are you doing here?

255
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:58,067
Paolo, I'll be the one
to tell your dad.

256
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:01,833
I want him to hear it from me.

257
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,567
Mom, are you sure?

258
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,400
Yes.

259
00:15:07,533 --> 00:15:09,567
I started this.

260
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:13,933
I'm the reason we were buried
in lies for a long time,

261
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:18,867
so I'll be the one
to tell him the truth.

262
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:21,900
I want this to end tonight.

263
00:15:22,033 --> 00:15:25,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:38,133
My child, don't stay up late.

265
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:40,867
And make sure you don't forget
to take your medicine.

266
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,833
Don't wait for us
or your father

267
00:15:42,967 --> 00:15:44,567
because we're going home too.

268
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:46,933
I have to go now.

269
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:48,500
They're about to call
your father, okay?

270
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:50,400
Good night, I love you.

271
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,033
Why are you here?

272
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,367
Who invited you?

273
00:15:54,933 --> 00:15:58,033
Marj, please. I don't have time
to argue with you.

274
00:15:58,167 --> 00:16:00,267
I'm looking for dad.
Where is he?

275
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,200
Bad timing for you to be here.

276
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:03,900
Don't interfere!

277
00:16:04,033 --> 00:16:05,833
What are you going to tell dad?

278
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,433
It's none of your business.

279
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,400
But if you're really curious,

280
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:15,067
you can come inside
to hear my grand reveal.

281
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,333
<i> And with that...</i>

282
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:18,033
Thea, wait. Come back here!

283
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:20,967
- Thea!
- A warm round of applause

284
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:25,100
to the chairman emeritus
of Torrecampo Realty.

285
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:27,300
Mr. Greg Torrecampo.

286
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:29,933
[APPLAUDING]

287
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:32,433
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:42,667
[LIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:52,467
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

290
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,167
I have built so many things
in my life.

291
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,867
Houses.

292
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,500
Buildings.

293
00:17:02,633 --> 00:17:04,067
I go all around.

294
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:07,667
I stand here tonight,

295
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:12,533
I realized that my greatest
achievement

296
00:17:12,667 --> 00:17:14,500
is not the empire I built.

297
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:19,500
It is the person
who will carry it over.

298
00:17:21,367 --> 00:17:24,667
To my son, Paolo Torrecampo...

299
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:28,967
[APPLAUDING]

300
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,900
You are my legacy.

301
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:36,733
You are the proof that
the blood of the Torrecampos

302
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:41,200
will remain strong
and successful

303
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,167
in the generations to come.

304
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:46,000
This is for you.

305
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:50,633
[APPLAUDING]

306
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:54,533
[LAUGHING]

307
00:17:58,133 --> 00:17:59,367
Wow!

308
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:04,000
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:11,133
Now this is more exciting.

310
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,933
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

311
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:18,767
How touching!

312
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,400
Stop it, Thea!

313
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:21,833
Why, Marj?

314
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,700
It's better when there are
lots of people

315
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:26,233
so there's audience impact.

316
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:27,400
[LAUGHS]

317
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:29,900
Guard, why did you allow someone
to cause trouble here?

318
00:18:30,033 --> 00:18:31,500
- [GASPS]
- Get this woman out!

319
00:18:31,633 --> 00:18:32,967
Relax!

320
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,400
Don't worry, Dad.

321
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:38,067
I have no intention
of staying here.

322
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,967
I just want to say
something to you.

323
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:46,000
Something mom has been hiding
from you for a long time.

324
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:49,733
What are you talking about?

325
00:18:51,067 --> 00:18:53,033
Stop it, Thea.

326
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:55,633
Can you please stop
making a scene here?

327
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,533
Is this it?

328
00:18:57,667 --> 00:18:59,367
[LAUGHS]

329
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:02,900
Is this what you were
so proud of,

330
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:06,233
continuing the Torrecampo
legacy?

331
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,300
Oh, my!

332
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:10,333
He doesn't deserve it, Dad.

333
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:15,567
In fact, he shouldn't even be
using the Torrecampo surname.

334
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:17,500
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

335
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:20,567
Thea, stop this!

336
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:21,200
No!

337
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,200
I will not stop.

338
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:28,000
Dad and the whole world
deserve to know the truth.

339
00:19:28,133 --> 00:19:33,733
That this man is the product
of infidelity by his mother

340
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,833
with another man!

341
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,600
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

342
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,733
He's not your blood, Dad!

343
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:45,167
He's not your real child!

344
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:57,367
You have a lot of nerve
to fabricate stories.

346
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,067
[GASPS]

347
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,400
Did Edward order you
to humiliate me?

348
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:05,300
To get back at me?

349
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:06,967
Security!

350
00:20:07,267 --> 00:20:10,100
Why is this woman still standing
in front of me?

351
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:12,800
Get her out of my sight now!

352
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,433
Mr. Torrecampo.

353
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,733
You don't have to throw her out,
Mr. Torrecampo.

354
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:21,600
Because there is nothing wrong
with telling the truth.

355
00:20:23,867 --> 00:20:25,233
Don't interfere here, Aldrin.

356
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:26,800
I'm not just interfering.

357
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:29,500
Because on the contrary,

358
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:33,733
I am deeply, personally involved
in all of this!

359
00:20:33,867 --> 00:20:36,600
Because Paolo is my brother.

360
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:40,400
Our father, Walter Belmonte,

361
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:43,900
had an affair with your spouse
a long time ago.

362
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:47,733
You don't believe it?

363
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:49,800
Why don't you ask your spouse?

364
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,233
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

366
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:15,533
Enough.

367
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:19,833
Enough!

368
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:26,233
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

369
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:42,433
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

370
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:56,667
Dad?

371
00:21:57,833 --> 00:21:59,567
Are you all right, Dad?

372
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:02,600
[SIGHS]

373
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,300
Yes, my child.

374
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:10,100
I hope you and grandfather
can make peace.

375
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:12,633
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:21,700
I've already been hurt so much
by your grandfather.

377
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:27,967
I don't know if I still want
to be his child.

378
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,067
You know, Dad,

379
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:35,700
when I found out I was actually
Uncle Paolo's child...

380
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:40,467
I was deeply hurt back then.

381
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,933
I felt like my own parent
gave me away.

382
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,367
I was angry at first.

383
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:52,167
But when I forgave Uncle Paolo,

384
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:54,467
I felt much lighter.

385
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,967
And maybe you should do
the same with grandfather.

386
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:04,700
Give him a chance.

387
00:23:04,833 --> 00:23:08,067
It's not too late
to fix your relationship, Dad.

388
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:12,167
So please don't give up
so easily.

389
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:17,467
["KATOTOHANAN"
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,667
Everybody out!

391
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:41,767
Now!

392
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:44,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

393
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,933
<i> Do you know how painful it is</i>

394
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,367
<i>that not even once I ever heard
you say you were proud of me?</i>

395
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:58,500
<i> What do you want?</i>

396
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:01,567
<i>Should I applaud you
even when you fail?</i>

397
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,100
<i>- Greg!
- Dad!</i>

398
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:05,500
<i>I've never done anything right
in your eyes!</i>

399
00:24:05,633 --> 00:24:07,100
<i> The way you treat me,</i>

400
00:24:07,233 --> 00:24:09,633
<i>it's like I'm not really
your child.</i>

401
00:24:09,767 --> 00:24:10,900
<i> From the very beginning,</i>

402
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:13,267
<i>you've only brought problems
to this family.</i>

403
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,767
<i>So, no matter what I do,
it's never enough for you?</i>

404
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:18,000
<i> The hell do I care about you?</i>

405
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:22,267
<i> Yes, Edward made mistakes,</i>

406
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:26,067
<i>but don't treat him
like he's not a human being.</i>

407
00:24:27,167 --> 00:24:28,600
If only I had known.

408
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:30,900
<i>Never go against
your older sibling.</i>

409
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:33,567
<i>If you don't want us
to have problems.</i>

410
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:36,967
<i>I'm your child too! I hope
you can be fair at least once!</i>

411
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:42,933
<i>If Edward fell short as a child,</i>

412
00:24:43,067 --> 00:24:47,167
<i>then you also fell short
as a parent!</i>

413
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:51,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:25:05,533 --> 00:25:09,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

415
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:21,467
Is it true?

416
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:28,833
Everything Thea
and Aldrin said...

417
00:25:30,467 --> 00:25:32,133
is it true?

418
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

419
00:25:43,733 --> 00:25:44,833
[SOBBING]

420
00:25:45,233 --> 00:25:47,033
I'm sorry, Greg.

421
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:49,900
I'm sorry.

422
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,633
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

423
00:25:52,767 --> 00:25:53,633
[CHOKING]

424
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:54,933
Sorry?

425
00:25:55,067 --> 00:25:59,633
After making me look like a fool
in front of the whole world?

426
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:07,233
I was cruel to my real child
because of your lies.

427
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:12,033
I destroyed Edward
because I believed...

428
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:14,833
he wasn't my blood.

429
00:26:14,967 --> 00:26:19,467
All of that
because of your infidelity!

430
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,667
Do you understand?

431
00:26:24,433 --> 00:26:26,433
Do you understand?

432
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:28,567
Did you hear that, Dad?

433
00:26:28,867 --> 00:26:32,100
The Torrecampos are slowly
self destructing,

434
00:26:32,333 --> 00:26:34,933
and I can imagine
your mistress Regina

435
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:38,833
feeling helpless and powerless

436
00:26:38,967 --> 00:26:40,933
while everything
is falling apart.

437
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:43,633
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

438
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:44,833
Dad, stop it!

439
00:26:44,967 --> 00:26:45,867
Please stop!

440
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,467
Marjorie, be quiet!

441
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,433
Edward and mom spent
their whole lives

442
00:26:49,567 --> 00:26:50,433
giving everything to you

443
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:53,300
just to please you
but you ignored them.

444
00:26:53,433 --> 00:26:54,967
You ruined their lives!

445
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:57,700
You destroyed all of our lives!

446
00:26:57,833 --> 00:26:58,800
Does it hurt?

447
00:26:58,933 --> 00:27:01,867
I'm not done getting revenge
on your mistress.

448
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:04,633
I still have many things
planned for her, Dad!

449
00:27:04,767 --> 00:27:06,167
I'm just getting started.

450
00:27:06,300 --> 00:27:08,133
No way! Never again!

451
00:27:08,267 --> 00:27:10,800
Because if you were truly good,
you wouldn't have stolen

452
00:27:10,933 --> 00:27:13,200
what should have gone
to my spouse and to us.

453
00:27:13,333 --> 00:27:15,800
Wait a second, who's really
greedy between the two of us?

454
00:27:15,967 --> 00:27:17,567
- [CLAMORING]
- You're the one who started

455
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:19,333
- all this chaos!
- [CLAMORING]

456
00:27:21,233 --> 00:27:22,333
Dad?

457
00:27:22,467 --> 00:27:24,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
